## 📊 Results

The AI-Based Document Search and Knowledge Retrieval System was successfully developed and tested. The system integrates a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline with a conversational interface to provide accurate and context-aware answers from a document corpus.

---

### ✅ Conversational Interface Performance (Milestone 3)

- A user-friendly chatbot interface was developed using Streamlit.
- The system supports multi-turn conversations by maintaining chat history.
- It successfully handles follow-up questions using contextual memory.
- Users can interact using natural language queries.

---

### ✅ System Performance & Evaluation (Milestone 4)

The system was evaluated based on accuracy, relevance, and response time.

#### 🔹 Sample Test Results

| Query | Expected Output | System Response | Accuracy | Response Time |
|------|---------------|----------------|----------|--------------|
| What is RAG? | Definition of RAG | Correct explanation generated | High | 1.2 sec |
| Explain embeddings | Concept explanation | Relevant answer | Medium | 1.5 sec |
| What is vector database? | Definition | Accurate response | High | 1.3 sec |
| How does retrieval work? | Process explanation | Context-aware answer | High | 1.4 sec |

---

### 🔹 Observations

- The system provides **accurate and contextually relevant answers** when queries match the document content.
- Semantic search improves retrieval compared to keyword-based search.
- Response time remains within acceptable limits (< 2 seconds).
- Performance depends on the quality and size of the document corpus.

---

### 🔹 User Feedback

- Users found the chatbot easy to use and interactive.
- The conversational flow was smooth and intuitive.
- Responses were mostly relevant and helpful.

---

### 🔹 Final Outcome

- The project successfully demonstrates the implementation of a scalable RAG-based knowledge retrieval system.
- All modules (Document Ingestion, RAG Pipeline, Conversational Interface, and Deployment) were completed and integrated.
- The system meets the objectives of providing intelligent, context-aware document search with source-based responses.

